Practice gives students the opportunity to participate in the organization of academic events (conferences, seminars), preparing research proposals (editing, translation) or preparing research publications (correspondence with authors, technical work on manuscripts, etc.) Practice links acquired knowledge with practical applications in different fields of research administration.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Practice aims to develop and support the retention of knowledge and skills related to research administration necessary in professional life. Practice gives students the opportunity to participate in the organization of academic events (conferences, seminars), preparing research proposals (editing, translation) or preparing research publications (correspondence with authors, technical work on manuscripts, etc.) Practice links acquired knowledge with practical applications in different fields of research administration.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The students who have completed practical training can apply knowledge in the speciality in a work situation, considering the social and cultural context; can connect knowledge and skills acquired earlier in the completion of work tasks; analyze their actions in solving practical professional problems in the speciality and assess them critically; have the experience of completing specific professional tasks and plan of action and can assess the results constructively.
